args: C'mon, how much trouble can one girl\ngive us? It's going to be past nightfall\nby the time we reach the village!
If she's reckless enough to take us on by\nherself, we'll just overwhelm her with\nour superior forces!
Look, she's gettin' tired!\nPush the attack!
*pant* *pant* No matter how relentless\nthe assault, I will never stop fighting\nto protect my friends!
I told you all this before, boy!\nWe don't have the means to fight.
So if the Empire wants something,\nwe just lie down and let them take it?!
If the choice is between that and death,\nit is no choice at all.
You will do no such thing!
But Sharena's out there fighting those\nbad Empire guys all by herself!
She went to take them down by herself\nso she could save her friends!
That woman is a damn fool...
No, she's not! She's my friend,\nand I'm going to help her!
Come with me, Father! Help me!\nTake everything you're feeling inside\nand use it to do something good!
...We can't do it, son. Not alone.
This is the end for you!
Don't fight alone! Surround them and\nkeep close watch on your neighbor!
Mathias, you brought the entire village!
I still think you're a meddling outsider,\nbut you're also clearly my son's friend—\nwhich means we can't leave you to die.
I asked my father to help you\nand he said yes!
But now you'll be caught in the fighting...
You pathetic hayseeds are no match\nfor the might and glory of the Empire!
Call for reinforcements! Don't stop until\nthe ground runs red with their blood!
This is terrible! I came here specifically\nto AVOID this outcome, but now...

We knew what we were getting into.
We don't have the means to fight.
Alone, the best we can hope for
is to buy a little time.
You know what it means to risk your life\nfor a friend—and I bet you have friends\nof your own who feel the same...
Alert! We just received notice that\nenemy forces have overrun our HQ!
Looks like we're just in time.
You continue to treat us like strangers\ninstead of friends, Sharena.
What are all of you doing here?
Did I not say before that I would be\nthere during your darkest hour?
Ain't like us not to come runnin'\nwhen a friend's in trouble!
How can there be so many of them?!\nTHIS IS JUST ABSURD!
And we've plenty more\nwhere they came from!
Oh, but this is so inspiring!
The Empire's attention was diverted\nbecause you were fighting them here.
That allowed the rest of us to sneak up\nand get the drop on them.
On top'a that, the villagers came to us\nrarin' to go. With them keepin' the soldiers\nbusy, their HQ was prime for the taking!
All of this is because of you, Sharena.\nYour natural magnetism and leadership\nhas moved mountains.
Oh, I'm so happy! *sniff* Ugh, and now\nmy nose is all snotty...
It's too soon to be letting up yet, folks.\nLet's wipe the floor with whoever's left!
Ha ha! That was toooo easy.
Ha ha, truth be told, I'm exhausted...\nBut exhilarated at the same time!
It's true, ma'am. We never could have\ndone all this without you.
You took on a whole array of imperial\nsoldiers without so much as blinking!
AND you overcame a desperate situation\nwith quick wits and true talent!
You really were amazing, ma'am.\nLike a hero from a faerie tale!
They're right, Sharena.\nYou're a hero today.
But still, if not for you coming to my aid,\nthis tale would have a very different end.
I was only able to persevere because\nall of you were there for me.
Heh. I can live with that.
Does that mean I was a hero too?
